    {% set content %}
        <p>Since its creation in 1939, the independent charity Citizens Advice has been a cornerstone of civic society: combined, the national organisation and network of 250 independent local <a class="link" href="https://assets.ctfassets.net/mfz4nbgura3g/1CvI8xMxxf8Qzm8uI2NKbF/ad0eec22a4379960bac66ca4ed5a84a4/Citizens_Advice_Annual_Report_2022-2023.pdf">Citizens Advice helped over 2.5 million people with one-to-one advice</a> last year.</p>
        <p class="mt-4">Citizens Advice advisors, both staff and volunteers, tackle a broad spectrum of complex issues, mirroring challenges faced by government departments. From tax inquiries to social services, frontline staff serve as the crucial link connecting the public with essential services.</p>
        <p class="mt-4">AI has the power to <a class="link" href="https://www.nber.org/papers/w31161">significantly enhance productivity in customer service environments</a>. Recognising this potential, Citizens Advice and the Incubator for Artificial Intelligence (i.AI) have collaborated to develop a product that will support their advisors, making it easier for their staff and volunteers to quickly find and share information with the people who come to the charity for help. </p>
        <p class="mt-4">Together, we’ve built a customer service Artificial Intelligence (AI) copilot service, affectionately dubbed Caddy, specifically built from the ground up to help customer service advisors and supervisors in quickly locating and sharing information from reliable sources.</p>
