            <h2 class="text-[24px] font-semibold">About Caddy</h2>
            <p class="mt-4">Caddy was born from a collaboration between i.AI and Citizens Advice Stockport, Oldham, Rochdale & Trafford (CASORT). This AI-powered assistant acts as a copilot for customer service agents, empowering them to provide high-quality, actionable advice quickly and securely.</p>
            <p class="mt-4">Building upon the initial prototype developed by CASORT, we have evolved Caddy into a scalable framework suitable for integration across government and beyond. Designed with interoperability in mind, Caddy seamlessly integrates into existing chat environments, harnessing widely-used open-source technologies for backend operations and employing infrastructure as code for swift deployment across cloud platforms.</p>
            <p class="mt-4">Caddy bases its advice on documentation provided to it. For the implementation at Citizens Advice, it uses a comprehensive range of public resources from GOV.UK and Citizens Advice, as well as Citizens Advice’s proprietary advice content. It can quickly incorporate any internal training materials, ensuring advice is always grounded in the most relevant information. A "human in the loop" validation system is employed to mitigate risk, ensuring advice accuracy and reliability.</p>
